\par After one of Nana\rquote s roast chicken dinners with baked sweet potatoes and homemade bread, I took the kids downstairs for their weekly boxing lesson.  Following the Monday-night fight with the kids, I glan
ced at my watch and saw that it was already a little past nine.
\par The doorbell rang a moment later.  I set down a terrific book called The Color of Water and pushed myself up from my chair in the family room.
\par \lquote I\rquote ll get it.  It\rquote s probably for me.\rquote   I called out.
\par \lquote Maybe it\rquote s Christine.  You never know.\rdblquote    Jannie teased, then darted away into the kitchen.  Both of the kids adored Christine, in spite of the fact that she was the principal at their school.
