ng else I had noticed at the tenement crime scene.  I also took the occasion to talk some more about the rash of unsolved murders in Southeast.  I went over the devastating stats I had compiled, mostly in my free time.
\par \lquote Statistic like that in Georgetown or the Capitol district, people in this city be enraged.  Going ballistic.  Be Washington Post headlines every day.  The president himself be involved.  Money no object.  National tragedy!\rquote 
  Jerome Thurman railed on and waved his arms around like signal flags.
\par \lquote Well, we are here to do something about it,\rquote  I said in a calmer voice.  Money is no object with us.  Neither is time.  Let me tell you what I feel about this killer,\rquote  I continued.  \lquote I think I know a few things about him.
\rquote 
\par \lquote How you come up with the profile?\rquote  Shawn Moore asked.  \lquote How can you stand thinking about these kinky bastards as much as you do?\rquote 
\par I shrugged.  \lquote It\rquote s what I do best.  I\rquote ve analyzed all the Jane Does,\rquote  I said.  \lquote It took me weeks working on my own.  Just me and the kinky bastard.\rquote 
\par \lquote Plus, he studies rodent droppings,\rquote  said Sampson.  \lquote I saw him bagging the little turds.  That s his real secret.\rquote 
\par I grinned, and told them what I had so far.  \lquote I think one male is responsible for at least some of the killings.  I don\rquote t think he\rquote s a brilliant killer, like Gary Soneji or Mr. Smith, but he\rquote 
s clever enough not to be caught.  He\rquote s organized, reasonably careful.  I don\rquote t think we\rquote ll find he has any prior record.  He probably has a decent job.  Maybe even a family.  My FBI friends at Quantico agree with that.
\par \lquote He\rquote s almost definitely caught up in an escalating fantasy cycle.  I think he\rquote s into his fantasies big time.  Maybe he\rquote 
s in the process of becoming someone or something new.  He might be forming a new personality for himself.  He isn\rquote t finished with the killing, not by any means.\rquote 
\par \lquote I\rquote ll make some educated guesses.  He hates his old self, though the people closest to him probably don\rquote t realize it.  He might be ready to abandon his family, job, any friends he has.  At one time he probably had very str
ong feelings and beliefs about something - law and order, religion, the government - but not anymore.  He kills in different ways - there\rquote s no set formula.  He knows a lot about killing people.  He\rquote 
s used different kinds of weapons.  He may have traveled overseas.  Or maybe he spent time in Asia.  I think it\rquote s very possible he\rquote s a black man.  He\rquote s killed several times in Southeast - no one\rquote s noticed him.\rquote 
