ven photographs of supposed lovers or victims.  Films were occasionally used and the other players had to decide whether or not the scenes were stage-acted or cinema verite.
\par Shafer couldn\rquote t imagine missing a chapter of the game himself.  Death was by far t
he most interesting character, the most powerful and original.  He had missed important social and embassy affairs just to be available for Thursday nights.  He had played when he had pneumonia, and once when he\rquote 
d had a painful double-hernia operation the day before.
