\par \lquote You\rquote re not fooling anybody, Cross, least of all me.  I\rquote m fully fucking aware that you\rquote re investigating homicides in Southeast that you aren\rquote t assigned to, the so-called Jane Does.  You\rquote 
re doing this against my explicit orders.  Some of those cases have been closed for over a year.  I won\rquote t have it, I won\rquote t tolerate your insubordination, your condescending attitude.  I know what you\rquote 
re trying to pull.  Embarrass the department, specifically embarrass me, curry fucking favor with the mayor, make yourself some kind of folk hero in Southeast in the process.\rquote 
\par I hated Pittman\rquote s tone and what he was saying, but I had learned one trick a long time ago, and it was probably the most important thing to know about politics inside any organization.  It\rquote s so simple, but it\rquote 
s the key to every petty kingdom, every fiefdom.  Knowledge truly is power; it\rquote s everything, and if you don\rquote t have any, pretend you do.
