o let him think that maybe I had some powerful connections with Mayor Monroe, and God only knows who else in the City on the Hill.  I let him think that maybe I was after his job, or that I might have, God forbid, even loftier aspirations.
\par \lquote I\rquote m working the homicides assigned to me.  Check with the captain.  I\rquote m doing my best to close as many cases as I can.\rquote 
\par Pittman nodded curtly - one nod.  His face was still heart-attack red.  \lquote All right, I want you to close this case, and I want you to close it fast.  A tourist was robbed and gunned down on M Street last night,\rquote  he said.  \lquote 
A well-respected German doctor from Munich.  It\rquote s front fucking page in today\rquote s Post.  Not to mention the International Herald Tribune, and every newspaper in Germany of course.  I want you on that murder case and I want it solved pronto.
\rquote 
