\par \lquote I\rquote m really happy for Damon.  He looks so proud up there.\rquote   I whispered to Nana and Jannie.  \lquote He is a handsome devil, too.\rquote 
\par \lquote Mr. Dayne is starting a girls\rquote  choir in the fall,\rquote  Jannie loud-whispered in my ear.\rquote You watch.  I mean, you listen.  I\rquote ll make it.\rquote 
\par \lquote Go for it, girl.\rquote   Nana said, and gave Jannie a hug.  She is very good at encouraging others.
\par Dayne suddenly called out loudly, \lquote Ugh.  I hear a swoop, I don\rquote t want any swoops here, gentlemen.  I want clean diction and pure pitch.  I want silver and silk.  I do not want swoops.\rquote 
\par Out of the corner of my eye, I suddenly saw Christine in the hallway.  She was watching Dayne and the boys, but then she looked my way.  Her face was principal-serious for just a moment.  Then she smiled and winked.
\par I walked over to see her.  Be still my heart.
\par \lquote That s my boy.\rquote   I said with mock proudness as I came up to her.  She was dressed in a soft gray pantsuit with a coral-pink blouse.  God, I loved seeing her now, being with her, hanging out, doing nothing, the works.
\par Christine smiled.  Actually, she laughed a little at me.  \lquote He does everything so damn well.\rquote  She didn\rquote t hold back, no matter what.  \lquote I was hoping you might be here, Alex,\rquote  she whispered.  \lquote 
I was just this very minute missing you like crazy.  You know that feeling?\rquote 
\par \lquote Yes, that feeling and I are well acquainted.\rquote 
\par We held hands as the choir practiced Bach\rquote s \lquote Jesu, Joy of Man\rquote s Desiring\rquote .  Everything felt so right, and it was hard to get used to.
\par \lquote Sometimes...  I still have this dream about George being shot and dying,\rquote she said as we were standing there.  Christine\rquote s husband had been murdered in her home, and she had seen him die.  It was one 
