\par I was a long way from where I\rquote d parked my car, but I was close to the Farragut apartment building.
\par I ran another hundred yards in the dark, then climbed the stone wall separating the zoo from the city streets.  There was blood smeared on my hands, and I didn\rquote t know where it had come from.  The knee I\rquote d scraped?  Scratch
es from swinging branches?  I could hear the loud wail of sirens in the near distance.  Was it coming from the Farragut?
