\par I hadn\rquote t gotten what I needed out there.  I hadn\rquote t been able to learn the truth from Shafer before he drowned.
\par Once or twice I glanced behind to make sure that Shafer wasn\rquote t following us, that he was gone.  There was no sign of him.  There was only the sound of our own, exhausted strokes cutting into the tide.
